title: Enock
description:
Although born with spina bifida and paralyzed from the waist down, Enock Glidden​ always held on to a lifelong dream of climbing Yosemite’s El Cap. This film shares the story of how he made the seemingly impossible feat a reality. His journey to the top of El Capitan began with support from the adaptive climbing organization Paradox Sports​ in a climbing gym. We want to help Paradox open doors for climbers of all abilities and are teaming up with them to help bring adaptive climbing techniques to gyms across the U.S.

Learn more here: https://www.thenorthface.com/paradoxsports

Director/Producer: Craig Muderlak, Muderlak Art

Music: 
'Cinematic Piano Background' - Josh Kramer
'Yearning Sentimental Background' - Josh Kramer
'All This Time' - Dan Phillipson
'Increase' - Craig Muderlak
'My Time With You' - Ben Beini
'I Would Have' - Craig Muderlak
